data.label:
Player_Romus

"Remind me again. How much do we have riding on this?"

Player_Romus

"I fully intend to come out of this building with both our gold income and our international relations intact, Ms. Werner."

Player_Romus

"Do you still think our proposal is a good idea?"

Player_Romus

"Yes. It's time for Morella to get its proper due."

Narrator

Alvarez had a smug expression on his face as I took my place next to him.

Alma Saltana

"In accordance with a majority of stakeholders, we have negotiated a draft proposal for the nationalization of the Trade Zone."

Alma Saltana

"I thank my partners for their generosity and cooperation during this process."

Narrator

The audience broke into animated whispers.

Player_Romus

"If the Republic of Morella deems this proposal to be the best choice, I have no other option but to agree to it."

Player_Romus

"Unfortunately, circumstances have changed. Though I worked closely on this proposal with Morella, I can no longer agree to it."

Player_Romus

"My kingdom is happy to approve this proposal."

Narrator

Both Saltana and Hegel stared at me in abject shock.

Alma Saltana

"Thank you, King Romus... Chancellor Hegel?"

Patricio Alvarez (R)

"Lespia votes no to this unfair sham of an agreement."

Player_Romus

"The Kingdom of Rizia had no part in this proposal and we refuse to approve it."

Player_Romus

"Unfortunately, circumstances have changed. Though we worked very closely with Morella on this proposal, we can no longer agree to it."

Alma Saltana

"Thank you, King Romus... Chancellor Hegel?"

Narrator

There was a round of polite applause.

Emmerich Hegel (R)

"The Republic of Valgsland cannot approve this proposal."

Narrator

Just as the door was being opened for us, an aide rushed up to Elena and whispered something in her ear.

Narrator

Her face turned white. She pulled me aside.

Elena Werner

"Especially if Hegel supports it as well..."

Narrator

Hegel looked me in the eye and nodded in greeting, his expression unreadable.

Player_Romus_Italic

I didn't acknowledge him.

Don't acknowledge him.

Narrator

He stopped in his tracks.

Player_Romus

"Of course I'm ready. It's not like anything is going to change."

Player_Romus

"There had better not be any unpleasant surprises."

Elena Werner

"Trust me. I know the signs of a coming uprising when I see one..."

Elena Werner

"I really am getting too old for this."

Narrator

Saltana gasped audibly. Alvarez didn't look surprised.

Alma Saltana

"It seems we do not have an agreement after all. The Meftiem International Trade Zone will not be nationalized."

Emmerich Hegel (R)

"The Republic of Valgsland cannot approve this proposal."

Narrator

The Morellan prime minister took a moment to compose herself.

Narrator

Elena cornered me as I came out of the room.

Elena Werner

"The day we're 'friendly' with Chancellor Hegel is the day I eat my own hat."

Player_Romus

"Enjoy the feeling, Mr. Prime Minister. You won't be happy for long."

Player_Romus

"I haven't forgotten about our arrangement."

Alma Saltana

"Several years ago, the Republic of Morella began an initiative to bring the resources of the Meftiem Basin under the stewardship of our state and our people."

Alma Saltana

"That is not the only gesture of faith that Chancellor Emmerich Hegel has extended to us."

Player_Romus

"I suppose you won't be happy to know that I promised Caleqabiz to the CSP."

Patricio Alvarez (R)

"Let's hope it doesn't come to that, Your Majesty."

Patricio Alvarez (R)

"But for how long, Your Majesty? This doesn't bode well for either of us."

Patricio Alvarez (R)

"Let's see if you can keep up that sanguine attitude when they come for your head."

Narrator

She took a deep breath.

Alma Saltana

"In this new agreement, each of our partners are able to keep their existing share. Nobody will be going home empty-handed."

Narrator

There was a round of polite applause.

Alma Saltana

"By a 3-1 vote, the renegotiated agreement for the Meftiem International Trade Zone will be implemented."

Narrator

Whispers rippled through the crowd. The Morellan prime minister took a moment to compose herself.

Narrator

She waved at all of us to join her at her podium for a photograph.

Narrator

Alvarez and Hegel stood on either side of us as Saltana held up the new contract for the cameras.

Narrator

Alvarez and Hegel both stepped next to Saltana as she held up the new contract for the cameras.

Narrator

Saltana tapped on her mic once more.

Narrator

She didn't respond. Her eyes stayed on the audience.

Player_Romus_Italic

I didn't react.

Don't react.

Player_Romus

"Justice? You will lead Merkopa into ruin."

Alma Saltana

"I will take questions shortly. For now, please talk amongst yourselves."

Narrator

Alvarez turned to me with a thin-lipped smile.

Patricio Alvarez (R)

"The gloves are off, Your Majesty. The best of luck to your kingdom."

Patricio Alvarez (R)

"Consider this the beginning of a beautiful friendship. Or something."

Narrator

The Lespian prime minister spoke into my ear, in a voice so low only I could hear it.

Patricio Alvarez (R)

"The gloves are off now, Your Majesty. Good luck in Pales."

Patricio Alvarez (R)

"That was painless, wasn't it, Your Majesty?"
